org.jscsi.target.scsi.sense.senseDataDescriptor.senseKeySpecific

Class SenseKeySpecificData

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jscsi.target.scsi.sense.senseDataDescriptor.senseKeySpecific.SenseKeySpecificData
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ISerializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ActualRetryCountSenseKeySpecificData, FieldPointerSenseKeySpecificData, InvalidSenseKeySpecificData, ProgressIndicationSenseKeySpecificData, SegmentPointerSenseKeySpecificData

    public abstract class SenseKeySpecificData
extends Object
implements ISerializable
    SENSE-KEY-SPECIFIC DATA further defines the reason for a CHECK CONDITION SCSI response status.

    The definition of the SENSE KEY SPECIFIC field is determined by the value of the enclosing sense data's SenseData.senseKey field.

    Sense Key Sense Key Specific Field Definition
    SenseKey.ILLEGAL_REQUEST Field Pointer (see FieldPointerSenseKeySpecificData)
    SenseKey.HARDWARE_ERROR,
    SenseKey.MEDIUM_ERROR, or
    SenseKey.RECOVERED_ERROR    		 Actual Retry Count (see ActualRetryCountSenseKeySpecificData)
    SenseKey.NO_SENSE or
    SenseKey.NOT_READY    		 Progress Indication (see ProgressIndicationSenseKeySpecificData)
    SenseKey.COPY_ABORTED Segment Pointer (see SegmentPointerSenseKeySpecificData)
    All other Sense Keys The sense key specific sense data descriptor shall not
    appear in the descriptor format sense data and the
    SKSV (Sense Key Specific Field Valid) bit shall be set to
    zero in the fixed format sense data.
    Author:
    Andreas Ergenzinger
